1
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,640
These are made by my uncle.

2
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,640
They only cost 19.9 yuan.

3
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:37,740
Aren't they better than those selling for over 100?

4
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:41,560
How does your uncle know how to do everything?

5
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,680
Of course. He's my uncle after all.

6
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,560
My uncle said,

7
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:48,759
take these glasses home first,

8
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,080
tell your parents

9
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:52,320
they only cost 19.9 yuan.

10
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:55,000
If your parents agree to pay,

11
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,320
bring the money to me tomorrow.

12
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:59,320
If they don't want to pay,

13
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:02,000
just return the glasses to me tomorrow.

14
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,000
Oh, and

15
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,320
don't break them.

16
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,440
You'll have to pay me 19.9 yuan if you do.

17
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,440
Great!

18
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,079
Uncle.

19
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,050
Eight classmates have paid

20
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:27,240
and the other two were taken by other students.

21
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,640
Not bad, kid.

22
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,880
Can I have another 100?

23
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,000
A hundred?

24
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,420
Can you really sell that many?

25
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,329
If I can't sell them, I'll bring them back.

26
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,200
Interesting.

27
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,560
Here you go.

28
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,760
Uncle,

29
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,820
I have another idea to share with you.

30
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,160
Wei.

31
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,600
Could you knock more quietly?

32
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,400
I thought it was a gambling raid.

33
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,960
I was knocking so loud.

34
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,020
I've been knocking for five minutes.

35
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,980
Look at all this fun. Hurry up.

36
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,250
Have a seat, Cui.

37
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,520
Give this to Huo.

38
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:18,700
What is this thing?

39
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,760
He loves Scottish bagpipes.

40
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,079
There's a tune called 'Amazing Grace'.

41
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,520
But those bagpipes are too big.

42
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,760
I couldn't find one to buy.

43
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:27,290
The sound is quite similar.

44
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,640
Will this work?

45
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,640
It will. Look, try it yourself.

46
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,450
What's going on?

47
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,640
I'm not dead.

48
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,200
You guys carry on.

49
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,450
That's terrifying.

50
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:12,160
They're saluting the music.

51
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,330
How's Erpang doing?

52
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,079
He's doing great.

53
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,959
He helped me sell 300 pairs of glasses the other day.

54
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:20,839
What glasses?

55
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,280
Pinhole glasses.

56
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,480
They correct vision.

57
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,640
You're making glasses again?

58
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,080
Yes.

59
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,040
I just started.

60
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:26,840
The first batch produced

61
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:27,900
over 10,000 pairs.

62
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:38,760
How is it?

63
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,640
Looks great.

64
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:41,320
Really cool,

65
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,159
man.

66
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,720
Twelve pairs in total.

67
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,520
Let me pay you.

68
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:48,840
No need.

69
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,400
Don't worry about it.

70
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,720
You really don't have to.

71
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,480
These are corrective glasses.

72
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,480
Is this enough?

73
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:54,520
We can adjust if needed.

74
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,400
200 is enough.

75
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:56,440
Twelve pairs.

76
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,850
Give me two hundred.

77
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:58,840
No.

78
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,400
Their eyesight is fine.

79
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,720
You don't actually need to buy them any.

80
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,280
Even good eyesight needs maintenance, right?

81
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:04,520
Their eyes are actually fine.

82
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,920
Even if you buy these, they won't wear them.

83
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,080
What card is this, Sanhua?

84
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,960
Is this a spade or a club?

85
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:13,960
Hey, Ermao!

86
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:14,720
Brother.

87
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,720
Hey, boss, where are you?

88
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:17,580
I can't see you.

89
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:18,760
Damn.

90
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:19,480
You guys...

91
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,520
So well-trained.

92
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,480
This is really something.

93
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,410
Without your glasses, you'll all go blind tomorrow.

94
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,840
You're short eleven pairs.

95
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:26,480
Walk me out. Let's go.

96
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,480
Take all of these.

97
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:28,730
Alright.

98
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,760
We must support your business.

99
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,850
But have you thought about something?

100
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:36,280
If one Erpang can sell so much at school,

101
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:39,920
what if we develop an Erpang in every school?

102
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,720
You're a genius!

103
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,180
It's like our fish market.

104
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:47,920
People come from many cities to buy our silver carp wholesale.

105
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:50,480
I have my brothers connect with each city.

106
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,840
This way we get more familiar,

107
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,480
and business keeps getting better.

108
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:57,000
Our city has over 100 primary and secondary schools.

109
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,000
If we develop an Erpang in each school,

110
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,260
you won't worry about sales anymore.

111
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,720
Erpang thinks just like you.

112
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:05,240
Genius.

113
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,200
I've been learning about business lately.

114
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,620
We have many brothers.

115
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,960
I can send my brothers

116
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,890
to help you expand to every school.

117
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:14,320
No.

118
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,410
No need, no need.

119
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,540
Don't be like that.

120
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:21,320
We've been doing legitimate business lately.

121
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:21,960
I know.

122
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,000
I believe you.

123
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,120
I'm going now.

124
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,600
Some of you

125
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,140
think this place is

126
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,200
too small,

127
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,920
too shabby,

128
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,440
too terrible.

129
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,200
So,

130
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,840
I want to tell you all a true story.

131
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,320
I discovered a company

132
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,000
called Sancheng.

133
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,080
Their founder

134
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,320
used to

135
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,480
sell salted fish and rice.

136
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,200
In 1979,

137
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,840
He bet all his capital.

138
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,240
And shifted to

139
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,450
the technology sector,

140
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,840
specifically the powerful semiconductor industry.

141
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,560
Today,

142
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:08,800
Sancheng

143
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,800
has become a world-class

144
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,200
semiconductor technology company.

145
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,060
Would you say that's impressive?

146
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:18,320
Tell me loudly,

147
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,480
is it impressive or not?

148
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,800
Impressive!

149
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,240
Our goal

150
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:26,080
is first to become Donglin's Sancheng Electronics,

151
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,560
and then to surpass Sancheng.

152
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:33,560
We will build our aircraft carrier here.

153
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:37,320
We will build our spaceship here.

154
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:39,080
Spaceship!

155
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:43,320
Great!

156
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:46,440
With my encouragement,

157
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,980
my uncle expanded production capacity.

158
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,800
For my first pot of gold,

159
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,040
I actively mobilized my friends

160
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,280
to join my money-making venture.

161
00:07:55,880 --> 00:08:00,160
We're using a system where we get the goods first and pay later.

162
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,800
Each of us

163
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,520
can get 100 pinhole glasses from me.

164
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:07,400
The wholesale price is 16 yuan,

165
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:11,080
and we'll set the retail price at 19.9 yuan.

166
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,240
In the first week,

167
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,480
if we can sell all these glasses,

168
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:18,440
then we'll be rich.

169
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,080
Say a few more words to us.

170
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:30,180
When will you take me along to make money?

171
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,200
Just focus on selling your barbecue.

172
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,200
I don't want to do barbecue anymore.

173
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,440
I want to join you in the pinhole business.

174
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,200
I'll give you two words:

175
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,100
Deep cultivation.

176
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,450
What does that mean?

177
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:43,559
It means that you,

178
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,320
no matter what business you're in,

179
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,800
you need to master it completely.

180
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,960
This way, whatever you do,

181
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,080
you can become

182
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,200
a boss,

183
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,960
or even a leader.

184
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,970
The prerequisite is

185
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,570
you must have the spirit of deep cultivation.

186
00:08:58,800 --> 00:08:59,860
Deep cultivation.

187
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,770
I'm going to take a leak.

188
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,160
Changed jobs four times in March.

189
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:11,240
Have you really committed to anything?

190
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,320
Can you sell these glasses any cheaper?

191
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,440
Can't do that.

192
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,600
We have a fixed price of 19.9.

193
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,760
Don't be so rigid.

194
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:19,880
Just sell them for 18.

195
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:21,480
Everyone will buy from you.

196
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,880
If you discount it by 1 yuan, I'll buy two pairs.

197
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,680
I'll buy a pair for my sister too.

198
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:29,520
Although Jingwei filling the sea is a mythological story,

199
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,360
however,

200
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,840
it contains very rich meaning.

201
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,320
Wang Ning.

202
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:45,720
Alright, 18.9 then.

203
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,320
Can't go any lower than that.

204
00:09:58,920 --> 00:09:59,840
Stop counting.

205
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,520
Let the bank count it.

206
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,040
If you make a mistake,

207
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,320
they certainly won't.

208
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,200
I go to the bank every day.

209
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,440
Everyone there knows me now.

210
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,840
They all ask what I do

211
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,570
to make so much money every day.

212
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,160
What did you tell them?

213
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,520
How could I tell them?

214
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,800
I said it's all earned by my husband.

215
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,530
I don't know anything about it.

216
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,460
How much have we saved?

217
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,440
We've saved

218
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,040
over 170,000.

219
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,400
No, that's not right.

220
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,200
Let me see.

221
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,920
With this week, it should be over 190,000.

222
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,920
Er Pang wants to organize another distribution meeting.

223
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:29,800
Probably

224
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,040
we can get another sum of money.

225
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,770
We're not far from 250,000 now.

226
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,840
Did you tell your father?

227
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,800
Of course I did.

228
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,080
Dad was so happy.

229
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,280
It proves that

230
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,320
Smart people are smart wherever they go.

231
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,280
I could help build a spacecraft,

232
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,680
so how could I not handle these few lousy glasses?

233
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:50,400
Really.

234
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,520
Just wait.

235
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,640
When I get my lawyer's license,

236
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:57,480
I'll post my results right on the factory bulletin board.

237
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,280
Look, there's money all over the bed.

238
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,740
It's so dirty. Take it out.

239
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,380
You're complaining that money is dirty?

240
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:16,560
Uncle Cui.

241
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:18,440
Can you come to my house?

242
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,320
My grandfather is dying.

243
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,560
What?

244
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:24,440
Hello?

245
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,840
My grandfather is dying.

246
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,200
Is he still alive?

247
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,800
Yes, he is.

248
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,330
Call 120 right away.

249
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,560
I did.

250
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,400
Wait at home.

251
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,530
I'll be right there.

252
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,160
Go to sleep.

253
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,200
What's wrong?

254
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,330
I need to go to the hospital.

255
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:46,740
Is our father sick?

256
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,400
No, it's Guo Dapao's father.

257
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,600
You scared me. It's the middle of the night.

258
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,560
Are you taking everything?

259
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,960
I'm taking it all anyway.

260
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,210
Go back to sleep.

261
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,840
What a rare visitor!

262
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:23,890
Who did you knock out this time?

263
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,040
You're not even injured.

264
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,450
A complete victory.

265
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,800
He's gone to the emergency room.

266
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,440
You're quite ruthless, kid.

267
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,930
Even worse than your brother-in-law.

268
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,440
Your brother-in-law hasn't been seen for days.

269
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,900
He's probably in jail now.

270
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,520
Your daughter...

271
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,260
The child is quite pretty.

272
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,080
But these clothes won't do.

273
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,940
Look at you all dressed up nicely.

274
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,720
While dressing the child like this.

275
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:55,160
They say raise girls rich and boys poor.

276
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:57,090
Girls should wear pretty clothes.

277
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,580
She's not my daughter.

278
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,800
Is it worth it?

279
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:00,800
Just buy some new clothes.

280
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,260
Don't abandon your child.

281
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,760
How is it?

282
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,120
We saved him.

283
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,020
But his condition isn't good.

284
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,120
How bad is it?

285
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,720
At best, he'll live a month or so.

286
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,360
And at worst?

287
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,160
Any time now.

288
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:21,410
Your father's hospital bills won't be cheap.

289
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,240
